
<refentry id="rndseed">
<indexterm id="IndexRndseed"><primary>rndseed</primary></indexterm>
  <refentryinfo><title>Signal Generators:Random (Noise) Generators</title></refentryinfo>
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>rndseed</refentrytitle>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>rndseed</refname>

    <refpurpose>
      Sets the global rndseed value.
    </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      Sets the global seed value for <link
      linkend="rnd"><citetitle>rnd</citetitle></link> and <link linkend="birnd"><citetitle>birnd</citetitle></link>.
    </para>
    <synopsis><command>rndseed</command> ival</synopsis>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Performance</title>
    <para>
      Use of <emphasis>rndseed</emphasis> will provide alternative
      results from the rnd and birnd opcodes to the default which is a
      seed of 0.5.
    </para>

    <para>
      When specifying a seed value, <emphasis>ival</emphasis> should
      be between 0 and 1.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

